Client -> Server messages:
Common structure for every message sent by client to server:
{
	"requester": "nameOfRequester",
	"request": "@RQST"
}

There are several requests that can be done:
- @CHAT, for a chat message (if receiver is "all" than message is sent to everybody)
{
	"requester": "nameOfRequester",
	"request": "@CHAT",
	"receiver": "nameOfReceiver",
	"message": "messageBody"
}
- @GAME, for a gameMove (tileList size goes from 1 to 3)
{
	"requester": "nameOfRequester",
	"request": "@GAME",
	"column": "numberOfColumnOfInsertion",
	"tileList": [
		{
			"column" : "numCol1",
			"row": "numRow1"
		},
		{
			"column" : "numCol2",
			"row": "numRow2"
		}
	]
}
- @LOGN, for login request
{
	"requester": "nameOfRequester",
	"request": "@LOGN",
	"nickname": "nickname",
	"gameMode": "gameModeType",
	"startGame": "startGame",
	"numOfPlayer": "numOfPlayer",
}
- @VPLA, for player-score update
{
	"requester": "nameOfRequester",
	"request": "@VPLA"
}
- @VCCA, for common cards names
{
	"requester": "nameOfRequester",
	"request": "@VCCA"
	"numOfCommonCards": 2
	"commonCard1": ...
	"commonCard2": ...
}


Server -> Client messages:
Common structure for every message sent by server to client (if receiver is 'all' than message is broadcasted)
{
	"receiver": "nameOfRequester",
	"request": "@RQST"
}

There are several updates that can be done:
- @CHAT, for a chat message (if receiver is "all" than message is sent to everybody)
{
	"receiver": "nameOfRequester",
	"request": "@CHAT",
	"receiver": "nameOfReceiver",
	"message": "messageBody"
}
- @BORD, for a board update
{
	"receiver": "nameOfRequester",
	"request": "@BORD",
	...
}
- @SHEL, for login request
{
	"receiver": "nameOfRequester",
	"request": "@SHEL",
	...
}
- @VCCA, for common-cards update (commonCardsList size goes from 1 to 2)
{
	"receiver": "nameOfRequester",
	"request": "@VCCA"
	"commonCardsList": [
		{
			"name": "nameOfCommonCards1",
		},
		{
			"name": "nameOfCommonCards2",
		}
	]
}
//TBD for players and score
- @VCCA, for common cards names
{
	"receiver": "nameOfRequester",
	"request": "@VCCA"
}


- @ERRO, for errors
{
	"receiver": "nameOfRequester",
	"request": "@ERRO",
	"errorType": "ERR_TYPE",
	"content": "error message"
}

ERR_TYPE can be seen in seqence diagram.







